To enact R.S. 33:9131 and R.S. 48:390.2, relative to blighted or abandoned railroads and
associated structures; to create a local railroad commission; to provide for board
members of the railroad commission; to provide for study requirements of the
commission; to provide for reporting requirements; to require railroad companies to
remove or remediate blighted or abandoned railroads and related structures within
one year; to ensure the preservation and upkeep of railroads, including painting and
rust removal, of underpasses; and to provide for related matters.
Notice of intention to introduce this Act has been published
as provided by Article III, Section 13 of the Constitution of
Louisiana.
Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
Section 1. R.S. 33:9131 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
§9131. Northwest Louisiana Railroad Commission; operation by railroad
commission
A. The Northwest Louisiana Railroad Commission, hereinafter referred to
as the "commission", is hereby created for the purpose of studying and reporting
findings and recommendations of any blighted or abandoned railroad crossings and
associated structures in the parishes of Bienville, Bossier, Caddo, Claiborne, Desoto,
Red River, and Webster.
B.(1) The commission shall be composed of one member appointed by the
governing authority of each parish referenced in Subsection A of this Section, one
member appointed by the office of multimodal commerce, the Department of
Transportation and Development to advise and assign staff to assist the commission
