in performing its duties, and the District 5 commissioner or his designee of the
Louisiana Public Service Commission.
(2) The commission shall hold its first meeting not later than January 1, 2027
at which the commission shall select a chairman from among its membership and
shall adopt rules of procedure, a work schedule, and any additional measures that it
deems necessary for the timely performance of its duties. The members of the
commission shall serve without compensation, and a vacancy in the membership
shall be filled in the same manner as the original appointment. A majority of the
members of the commission shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of business.
The commission shall be domiciled in Shreveport, Louisiana but may hold meetings
elsewhere in the state.
(3) The commission shall meet biannually or as often as the chairman of the
board convenes it, or on written request of any member.
C.(1) In conducting its study, the commission shall, at a minimum, do all of
the following:
(a) Identify what railroads and associated structures require remediation or
removal.
(b) Create a procedure for assessing and classifying the various conditions
of railroads and associated structures pursuant to 49 CFR Part 213.
(c) Create a procedure for providing notice to railroad companies of the
inadequate condition of their railroads.
(d) Maintain, inspect, and retain records to ensure railroads meet the
minimum conditions and standards for its designated class.
(2) The commission shall submit a written report of its findings and
recommendations relative to all of the study requirements provided in Paragraph (1)
of this Subsection and any other matters related to railroad accountability that it
deems appropriate to the House Committee on Transportation, Highways, and Public
Works and the Senate Committee on Transportation, Highways, and Public Works
not later than July 1, 2027.
